            "answer_text": "In the battle it is estimated that nearly 1,857,619 troops died in total. Of that 1,857,619 solders, 1,129,619 were soldiers of the Red Army. In total, the Red Army had 478,741 missing solders or dead solders, and 650,878 troops got wounded or sick. The Soviets lost 2,769 aircraft, 4,341 tanks, and 15,728 guns. The Axis powers lost roughly 728,000 troops. They also lost 900 aircraft, 1,500 tanks, and 6,000 guns. Sources: Battle of Stalingrad ",
